race.comment: Very tough race. HOT TOO GO (7) backs up from last week at Caulfield, sticking on well for a narrow fourth, albeit with favours there. He should be better for that first go at 2400m and maps for every chance again here in a race that lacks star power. COMMANDER HARRY (1) was just fair in the Ararat Cup last time but had been good in a couple of other country cups prior. Tricky draw here but he can run well. PROCHESTER (14) looks set to peak rising to 2540m here fourth up. His last start over 2015m was the best of the campaign and he'll be running on late. KARBURAN (3) struggled in a better race over 2800m at Flemington last time but had been racing well prior and this suits. Takes catching. MICKIO (9) is going well and an each way hope.
